Package: westMR
Title: Finite Mixture Regression with Variable and Effect-Type Selection
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Tulio", "Martins", email = "tbatista@uoguelph.ca", role = c("aut", "cre")),
      person("Jackson", "Mitchell", email = "jmitch19@uoguelph.ca", role = c("aut")))
Description: Implements finite mixture regression models for Gaussian, Poisson,
    and binomial responses, with procedures for selecting predictors and
    determining whether covariate effects are heterogeneous or homogeneous across
    mixture components. Estimation is performed using EM algorithms,
    with weighted least squares and structured QR decompositions used in the
    M-step.
